main event: A radar observation of an unidentified object at Montauk AFS, LI, N.Y. on November 5, 1959.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 10 minutes and was conducted via ground radar., The object was tracked climbing steadily to a range of 43 miles and an altitude of 78,200 feet., The radar blip was noted to be 1/8th inch wide on the radar screen., The conclusion of the report suggested that the object was a balloon., The report was prepared by SSGT Donald E Woods from the New York ADS Intelligence Division.
witness description: Clarence Nason, TSGT, 773D RADRON (SAGE), Radar Operator, estimated reliable.
